This paper deals with probabilistic programming languages and their semantics, which are typically studied in the programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also discusses Markov chain Monte Carlo algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper touches on error analysis and convergence results, which are topics of interest in information theory (cs.IT).
